Posting Description:
Aon is looking for an Data Scientist
Aon Risk Services, Inc. of Maryland seeks a Data Scientist in New York, New York to build database systems.
Your impact as an Data Scientist
Job Responsibilities:
Building, deploying, and maintaining machine learning (predictive) models for quantifying Intellectual Property (“IP”) risk and analytics;
Performing risk assessments to quantify IP risk using machine learning and statistical models;
Building and maintaining dashboards (visualizations) in Power BI and Tableau for IP datasets;
Identifying, preprocessing (data cleaning, wrangling), and analyzing datasets to enhance modeling capabilities. Resolve data inconsistencies and validate and clean data;
Performing data mining using Python, R, and Matlab;
Analyzing data using statistical packages including NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, and PyMC;
Building mathematical and machine learning models on public cloud servers including AWS and Azure; Organizing data using distributed version-control systems including GIT;
Building and deploying mathematical and machine learning models;
Applying the results from mathematical modeling and data exploration to conduct financial feasibility studies and market sizing analysis for new business opportunities;
Designing, building, and querying database systems for data retrieval using SQL;
Explore datasets using exploratory data analysis;
Building ETL pipelines to enable reporting, analysis, and data synchronization.
All positions require an applicant who has accepted an offer to undergo a background check.
You Bring Knowledge and Expertise
Requirements: Master’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field, plus six months of building database systems experience. Master’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field, plus six months of building database systems experience.
To apply, please send resume to aonresumes@aon.com and cite requisition number 00601, apply at jobs.aon.com, or click the apply button. This notice is subject to Aon Risk Services, Inc. of Maryland’s employee referral program.
We offer you
A competitive total rewards package, continuing education & training, and tremendous potential with a growing worldwide organization.
Our Colleague Experience:
From helping clients gain access to capital after natural disasters, to creating access to health care and retirement for millions, Aon colleagues empower results for our clients, communities, and each other every day. They make a difference, work with the best, own their potential, and value one another. This is the Aon Colleague Experience, defining what it means to work at Aon and realizing our vision of empowering human and economic possibility. To learn more visit Aon Colleague Experience.
About Aon:
Aon plc (NYSE:AON) is a leading global professional services firm providing a broad range of risk, retirement and health solutions. Our 50,000 colleagues in 120 countries empower results for clients by using proprietary data and analytics to deliver insights that reduce volatility and improve performance.
By applying for a position with Aon, you understand that, should you be made an offer, it will be contingent on your undergoing and successfully completing a background check consistent with Aon's employment policies. Background checks may include some or all of the following based on the nature of the position: SSN/SIN validation, education verification, employment verification, and criminal check, search against global sanctions and government watch lists, fingerprint verification, credit check, and/or drug test. You will be notified during the hiring process which checks are required by the position.
Aon provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, creed, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, veteran, marital, or domestic partner status. Aon is committed to a diverse workforce and is an affirmative action employer.
